newsitem.title: USA: U.S. Spring/White Wheat - Spring bids mixed.
newsitem.headline: U.S. Spring/White Wheat - Spring bids mixed.

text.p: Dark northern spring wheat values were mixed on Thursday.
Movement was sporadic. One dealer noted lackluster sales in Minnesota areas but others reported some farmer sales in several North Dakota and Montana locations.
A Minnesota dealer said the basis for spring wheat has a softer tone. "The market is waiting for some export business," he said.

He added spring wheat was almost trading on the same level as winter wheat. Usually it is higher, he said. "Most of the stuff (spring wheat) is 13 percent protein," he said, adding there seems to be no big premium for wheat with high protein content.
A Montana dealer agreed, saying spring wheat is still higher than winter wheat but it has a smaller premium, basis the protein content.
MGE spring wheat closed higher on short covering with September up two cents at $4.63-1/2 a bushel.
